::Bloodystrike::

Bloodystrike nods slowly, watching Snitch and wondering if the little 
bot would go totaly insane any time soon. It certainly seemed like it.

"Er, allright, can you write that down for me?"

He was wondering why this bot needed seventeen pretty looking rocks, 
but that was none of his business.

> ::Snitch::

> "3.85962103 Jigawatts of processed Energon, one quantum computer 
logistical
> gravimetric regulator, two RME level fifteen quadric-electric tri-
prong
> stabilizers, t'irdy foot copper wire, an' seventeen pretty looking 
rocks.
> Plus Snitch fill jet-packs fuel tanks and give two cartons ammo for 
each
> gun, free from charge, eh." The little monkey smiles at something 
funny that
> obviously only exists in his own little world.
